ose of the present volume of collected papers to examine whether and how the categories of "Primary and secondary religion" developed by T. Sundermeier and J. Assmann can be used to describe this change. The volume combines contributions from various disciplines (Theology/Old Testament Studies, Egyptology, Ancient Oriental Studies, Classical Studies and Religious Studies).  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aSociology, BiblicalvCongresses. 4aIsrael (Altertum). 4aReligion. 4aReligionsgeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aHistory of religion.  aIsrael (antiquity).  areligion.1 aAssmann, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBons, Eberhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBordreuil, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkert, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiesel, Anja A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrünschloß, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKessler, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLang, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoprieno, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNissinen, Martti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSallaberger, Walther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchipper, Bernd U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmid, Konrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitt, Rüdiger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab